 \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napoleon\"}, {\"begin\": 643, \"end\": 649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.767559996271987, \"rank\": 0.24533893962114242, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 535}, {\"ngram\": \"the fans\", \"from\": 537, \"to\": 545}, {\"ngram\": \"a setting\", \"from\": 551, \"to\": 560}, {\"ngram\": \"the 33rd Olympiad\", \"from\": 607, \"to\": 624}, {\"ngram\": \"a century\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 671}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago athletes cried alone in empty stadiums due to the Covid-19 outbreak, residents of Tokyo had a Games forced upon them during a major pandemic and fans were denied the greatest show on earth.\", \"from\": 674, \"to\": 879, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 772, \"end\": 777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999672062538872, \"rank\": 0.00032804497387954644, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 690, \"to\": 698}, {\"ngram\": \"empty stadiums\", \"from\": 714, \"to\": 728}, {\"ngram\": \"the Covid-19 outbreak\", \"from\": 736, \"to\": 757}, {\"ngram\": \"residents\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 768}, {\"ngram\": \"a Games\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 789}, {\"ngram\": \"a major pandemic\", \"from\": 814, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 839}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest show\", \"from\": 852, \"to\": 869}, {\"ngram\": \"earth\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 878}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There was a risk, should Paris have fallen flat, that our global love of the Olympics could fade as interest in the ancient ancestor across the Peloponnese did thousands of years ago.\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 1064, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 906, \"end\": 911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.874315120762801e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1025, \"end\": 1036, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peloponnese\", \"score\": 0.9999995606914182, \"rank\": 4.3930865243878616e-07, \"text\": \"Peloponnese\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peloponnese\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Peloponnese\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a risk\", \"from\": 891, \"to\": 897}, {\"ngram\": \"our global love\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 950}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 966}, {\"ngram\": \"interest\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 989}, {\"ngram\": \"the ancient ancestor\", \"from\": 993, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"thousands\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1050}, {\"ngram\": \"years\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1059}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Stay ahead with our three daily briefings delivering all the key market moves, top business and political stories, and incisive analysis straight to your inbox.\", \"from\": 1066, \"to\": 1226, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our three daily briefings\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"all the key market moves\", \"from\": 1119, \"to\": 1143}, {\"ngram\": \"top business\", \"from\": 1145, \"to\": 1157}, {\"ngram\": \"political stories\", \"from\": 1162, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"incisive analysis\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1202}, {\"ngram\": \"your inbox\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1225}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And it nearly did with the opening ceremony which, while ambitious, was underwhelming in its majority.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1330, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1271}, {\"ngram\": \"its majority\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1329}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Paris has been a triumph.\", \"from\": 1332, \"to\": 1361, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1336, \"end\": 1341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.874315120762801e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a triumph\", \"from\": 1351, \"to\": 1360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been a Games of celebration where nations are winning their first gold medals and established athletes are being beaten by lesser known challengers.\", \"from\": 1362, \"to\": 1517, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a Games\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1381}, {\"ngram\": \"celebration\", \"from\": 1385, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"nations\", \"from\": 1403, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"their first gold medals\", \"from\": 1423, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"established athletes\", \"from\": 1451, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"lesser known challengers\", \"from\": 1492, \"to\": 1516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's shown off one of the world's most beautiful cities, using it - and its admittedly dirty river Seine - perfectly to integrate culture, sport and spectacle.\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1678, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the world's most beautiful cities\", \"from\": 1541, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"Seine\", \"from\": 1618, \"to\": 1623}, {\"ngram\": \"culture\", \"from\": 1649, \"to\": 1656}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1663}, {\"ngram\": \"spectacle\", \"from\": 1668, \"to\": 1677}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Games have used the Palace of Versailles, Champs-\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es and Grand Palais for Equestrian, triathlon and taekwondo, captivating onlookers who have been absorbed by their surroundings.\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1866, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Games\", \"from\": 1680, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"the Palace\", \"from\": 1700, \"to\": 1710}, {\"ngram\": \"Versailles\", \"from\": 1714, \"to\": 1724}, {\"ngram\": \"Champs\", \"from\": 1726, \"to\": 1732}, {\"ngram\": \"\\u00c9lys\\u00e9es\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1740}, {\"ngram\": \"Grand Palais\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1757}, {\"ngram\": \"Equestrian\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"triathlon\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1783}, {\"ngram\": \"taekwondo\", \"from\": 1788, \"to\": 1797}, {\"ngram\": \"captivating onlookers\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 1820}, {\"ngram\": \"their surroundings\", \"from\": 1847, \"to\": 1865}]}, {\"sentence\": \"From Celine Dion's stunning rendition of L'Hymne \\u00e0 l'Amour to Julien Alfred's 100m surprise; the Olympic Games have restored the warming feeling lost through lack of atmosphere in Rio and absence of fans in Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 2081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1873, \"end\": 1884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.284960967996445e-38, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 2048, \"end\": 2051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999789131624811, \"rank\": 2.108728219827609e-05, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2075, \"end\": 2080, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.999672062538872, \"rank\": 0.00032804497387954644, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"L'Hymne \\u00e0 l'Amour\", \"from\": 1909, \"to\": 1926}, {\"ngram\": \"Julien Alfred's 100m surprise\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1959}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1961, \"to\": 1978}, {\"ngram\": \"the warming feeling\", \"from\": 1993, \"to\": 2012}, {\"ngram\": \"lack\", \"from\": 2026, \"to\": 2030}, {\"ngram\": \"atmosphere\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2044}, {\"ngram\": \"absence\", \"from\": 2056, \"to\": 2063}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 2067, \"to\": 2071}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But as good an Olympic Games as these were they have highlighted perfectly the politicisation of sport and the potential problems that come with it.\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2231, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"good an Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2090, \"to\": 2111}, {\"ngram\": \"the politicisation\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2176}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 2180, \"to\": 2185}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential problems\", \"from\": 2190, \"to\": 2212}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many, besides the Netherlands selectors it seems, agree that Steven van de Velde - a Dutch beach volleyball player who was convicted of raping a 12-year-old British girl in 2016 - should not have been at the games, despite serving his (albeit short) sentence.\", \"from\": 2233, \"to\": 2492, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2251, \"end\": 2262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"score\": 0.9999961038205087, \"rank\": 3.419877420370947e-06, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands\"}, {\"begin\": 2301, \"end\": 2313, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Charles_William_Meredith_van_de_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999999836304597, \"rank\": 1.636963145495452e-08, \"text\": \"van de Velde\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", 